tions of species and to vegetation spatial heterogeneity. Our study emphasizes that tropical soundscapes need to be recorded and analyzed in considerable spatial and temporal detail to understand their dynamics without the presence of human produced noise. Our analysis also suggests that tropical forests are unique places for acoustic diversity, supporting the need for preservation from all perturbations including anthropic noise. {\textcopyright} 2013 Elsevier B.V.},
